<item>
            <title>[NET-529] SubnetUtils throws exception on valid input</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-529</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think that xx.yy.zz.aa/0 should be accepted value by SubnetUtils, where xx.yy.zz.aa is any valid IPv4 IP address.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test case:&lt;br/&gt;
SubnetUtils subnetUtils = new SubnetUtils(&quot;10.10.10.10/0&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However it throws exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Value &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; not in range (0,32]&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.commons.net.util.SubnetUtils.rangeCheck(SubnetUtils.java:304)&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.commons.net.util.SubnetUtils.calculate(SubnetUtils.java:229)&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.commons.net.util.SubnetUtils.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(SubnetUtils.java:52)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I have updated issue description from original, to reflect that issue is not only with 0.0.0.0/0)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
